# LabFlow Project

This is an automated lab assignment project managed by LabFlow.

## Configuration
All project metadata is stored in `labflow.yaml`. Agents read it automatically.

## Structure
- `labflow.yaml` — project config (student, university, subject, lab details)
- `TASK.md` — extracted requirements from the guide PDF (created by planner)
- `src/` — source code (if applicable)
- `notebooks/` — Jupyter notebooks (if applicable)
- `images/` — screenshots and figures
- `docs/report.typ` — Typst report source
- `docs/report.pdf` — compiled PDF report
- `docs/template.typ` — Typst template (auto-generated)
- `STUDY_MATERIAL.md` — study notes and Q&A (optional)

## Commands
- `/init` — initialize a new lab project (creates structure, config, template)
- `/solve` — run full pipeline: parse guide → solve → write report → compile PDF
- `/study` — generate study materials with theory and control questions

## Rules
- All text output (comments, reports, UI) must be in Russian unless specified otherwise.
- Never modify `labflow.yaml` without explicit user request.
- Always compile Typst to PDF and verify the output before finishing.
- If any information is missing from config, check `~/.labflow.yaml` first, then ask the user.
